<section xml:id="section-assignment-week2">
  <title>Week 2 Assignment</title>
  <p><ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        Let <m>u</m> and <m>v</m> be vectors in <m>\RR^n</m>. Prove that
        <m>|u|^2 + |v|^2 = |u+v|^2</m> if and only if <m>v \perp u</m>.
        (Since this is an `if an only if' proof, make sure that the
        proof works in both directions.) (8) 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Let <m>u</m> and <m>v</m> be nonzero vectors in <m>\RR^3</m>.
        Assume that <m>u</m> is not a multiple of <m>v</m>. Let
        <m>w</m> be another vector in <m>\RR^3</m> such that both <m>u
        \times w = 0</m> and <m>v \times w = 0</m>. Prove that
        <m>w</m> must be the zero vector. (Hint: first prove that the
        cross product ofa ny two vectors is zero only if they are
        multiples of each other.) (6) 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Find the angle between these pairs of vectors. (You can give
        answers in approximate values. Show the steps in your
        calculation using the definitions from the course.) (9)
        <ol>
          <li><md>
            <mrow>
              \amp \begin{pmatrix}
                -5 \\ -7 
              \end{pmatrix}
              \amp \amp 
              \begin{pmatrix}
                0 \\ 4 
              \end{pmatrix}
            </mrow>
          </md></li>
          <li><md>
            <mrow>
              \amp \begin{pmatrix}
                0 \\ 2 \\ 2 
              \end{pmatrix}
              \amp \amp 
              \begin{pmatrix}
                -5 \\ -1 \\ -8 
              \end{pmatrix}
            </mrow>
          </md></li>
          <li><md>
            <mrow>
              \amp \begin{pmatrix}
                0 \\ 1 \\ -4 \\ -2 \\ -5
              \end{pmatrix}
              \amp \amp 
              \begin{pmatrix}
                3 \\ 3 \\ 0 \\ -2 \\ -5
              \end{pmatrix}
            </mrow>
          </md></li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol></p>
</section>
